<paragraph blockId="33.[192,1440,195,699]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis box="[240,370,643,667]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Etymology</emphasis>
—This species is named 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blahnik &amp; Holzenthal" authorityYear="2017" box="[685,813,643,667]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Mortoniella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="silacea">
<emphasis box="[685,813,643,667]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">M. silacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Latin word 
<emphasis box="[1092,1190,643,667]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">silaceus</emphasis>
, the color of yellow ochre, and referring to the color of the forewings of this species.
</paragraph>
